<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Embassy in the United Kingdom</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d176</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">176</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-05-22T13:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-05-22T13:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-22T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/5–2148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret   us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_Niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-22T14:00:00-04:00">May 22, 1948—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1877. For <persName corresp="#p_DLW1">Douglas</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_LRA1">Lovett</persName>. Proceed along lines indicated <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 2214,<note n="1" xml:id="d176fn1">May 21,
                            <ref target="#pg_266">p. 266</ref>.</note> endeavoring to persuade
                    French and checking British position re your suggestion concurred in by
                        <persName corresp="#p_CGLD1">Clay</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Reber</persName>. Do not
                    commit us as we need time to get top level clearance here.</p>
                <p>Assume <persName corresp="#p_CGLD1">Clay</persName> has taken into account that
                    announcement concerning provisional govt may give Soviets excuse to intensify
                    pressure in Berlin, also that US and British Delegations feel danger of delay in
                    Germany is greater than risks involved in Soviet reaction.<note n="2" xml:id="d176fn2">In telegram 2233, May 24, from London, not printed,
                        Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DLW1">Douglas</persName> confirmed that the
                        assumptions stated here were correct (740.00119 Council/5–2448).</note>
                        [<persName corresp="#p_LRA1">Lovett</persName>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
